ACTOR Chadwick Boseman's death has left many people filled with sadness around the world. Tributes have been pouring in from all over the world on social media. Mzansi celebs have also reacted to his death and paid tribute to the Black Panther actor. The Marvel star died on Friday after losing his battle to colon cancer. A statement was released to announce his death via his social media platforms. He was diagnosed in 2016, but still starred in movies such as Black Panther, 21 Bridges, Da 5 Bloods and Avengers: Endgame, just to mention a few. Celebs such as Sizwe Dhlomo, Masasa Mbangeni, Katlego Danke and Lady Zamar took to social media to appreciate the actor. Damn! Chadwick Boseman had cancer kanti? ?? RIP No!!! I can’t believe this! Such a humble, talented soul. Death be not proud! I am in disbelief ?? #WakandaForever #ChadwickBosemanForever #ripchadwickboseman pic.twitter.com/WoxPD71clN  Most of the celebs were marveled at the fact that he had cancer, but still continued to act. Masasa tweeted: "I can’t believe Chadwick Boseman gave us so much work & at the same time was battling colon cancer." Gomora actress Katlego shared a video of Chadwick surprising fans and tweeted: "It’s not just a role. It’s not just a story. It’s not just make believe. It touches lives, people are moved, people feel respected & represented. Thank u @chadwickboseman for your contribution to the story of black people. RIP King." Pearl Thusi thanked him for contributing group the arts: "Rest in eternal Peace Chadwick Boseman. Just found out he was diagnosed with colon cancer in 2016 & continued to work through treatments. Thank you, Chadwick for your incredible contribution to the arts! Your legacy will live on forever!